  "prompt": "Who is the best prime minister India has ever had?",
  "response": "Opinions on who the best prime minister of India has been can vary significantly based on personal views, political beliefs, and historical perspectives. Some commonly mentioned names include:\n\n1. **Jawaharlal Nehru** (1947-1964) - India's first prime minister, who played a crucial role in shaping the newly independent country and establishing democratic institutions.\n2. **Indira Gandhi** (1966-1977, 1980-1984) - Known for her strong leadership and controversial decisions, such as the Emergency period.\n3. **Atal Bihari Vajpayee** (1996, 1998-2004) - Recognized for his efforts in improving India\u2019s economy, infrastructure development, and fostering better international relations.\n4. **Narendra Modi** (2014-present) - Commended by supporters for his economic policies, strong leadership, and efforts to improve national security.\n\nUltimately, views on who is the \"best\" prime minister may differ based on individual priorities and criteria for leadership.",
